  "market_context": "USD/JPY printed a reversal candle on the weekly time frame, establishing a bullish bias for the week. Price was expected to expand higher with a shallow opposing run forming the wick of candle 3 before continuation upward into previous highs.",
  "key_observation": "The 15-minute retracement into a fair value gap left failure swings on the highs and printed a change in state of delivery, but the initial opposing run was too large to chase the reversal directly, requiring a continuation entry after a new protected swing formed.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify weekly reversal candle on USD/JPY, establishing bullish bias and expectation for expansion higher this week.",
    "On the 4-hour, observe expansion followed by a slow shallow retracement into a fair value gap, leaving failure swings on the highs as a candle 2 closure.",
    "Drop to the 15-minute time frame to look for an entry off the previous candle's low (21:00 / 01:00 candle).",
    "Note that price ran down with too large an opposing range, so skip the initial reversal entry since it would require expansion-met-with-expansion (bearish).",
    "Wait for a change in state of delivery as price expands back up through the down-close candles.",
    "Identify the new protected swing: price hits a short-term target, retraces into a fair value gap, and closes over the down-close candle into it.",
    "Take continuation entry with stop below the protected swing, targeting 2.45R to the prior highs.",
    "Avoid extending beyond the 09:00 candle close since expansion candles have limited range and time."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade reached the 2.45R target at the prior highs (target hit, ~16.9 points / $50,244.93 shown on chart).",
  "lessons": "When the initial opposing run is too large to trade the reversal directly, wait for a new protected swing after a change in state of delivery and take a continuation entry, provided 2R+ remains available to the target.",
